        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 6:08PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 608 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Victor, or 19 miles southwest of Colorado Springs,
moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Victor, Pueblo West, Pinon, Penrose, and Canon City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
